properties.Name: ClaimFraud
properties.Description: Intentional lying or concealment by policyholders to obtain payment of an insurance claim that would otherwise not be paid, or lying or misrepresentation by the insurance company managers, employees, agents, and brokers for financial gain.

Columns.Name: ClaimId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of a Claim.

Columns.Name: FraudId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of a fraudulent activity.

Columns.Name: ClaimFraudTypeId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of a Claim Fraud Type.

Columns.Name: FraudCommittedTimestamp
Columns.Description: The timestamp that the fraud was committed.

Columns.Name: FraudReportedDate
Columns.Description:
The date that the fraud was reported.

Note:
This may more likely to be known precisely than the date that the fraud was committed.

Columns.Name: FraudLossAmount
Columns.Description: The amount resulting from the fraud.

Columns.Name: FraudResolutionMethodId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of a fraud resolution method.

Columns.Name: LegalOutcomeStatement
Columns.Description: A statement describing the results or outcome of the legal action against the party for fraud.

Columns.Name: PaymentCardFraudNote
Columns.Description: A note, comment or additional information regarding the Payment Card Fraud.
